# Brand Specification

## Purpose

This document defines the visual identity of CAP Market: the logo, its approved variations, and the current status of brand colors. It exists so that anyone — designer, developer, or AI — uses the correct, current assets rather than guessing or inventing new ones.

This document does not cover Vision or Mission (see PH-001) or Customer Experience (see PH-003).

---

# Logo

## Concept

The CAP Market mark is a circular "C" form (echoing both "CAP" and "circle of provision") built from a basket containing a grain stalk, leaves, and produce. The open arc of the "C" doubles as the basket's rim.

Design intent, as stated by the concept itself:

- Simple
- Memorable
- Scalable
- Timeless
- Trusted

## Approved Variations

Two lockups are confirmed and available for use. Each exists in both a transparent-background export and a white-background export.

### 1. Icon Only

The circular basket mark on its own, with no wordmark. Used where space is limited or the mark needs to stand alone — app icon, favicon, social profile image, packaging accents.

### 2. Horizontal Lockup

Icon on the left, paired with the "CAP MARKET" wordmark and the tagline "ABUNDANCE · HEALTHY FOOD · CONVENIENCE" stacked beneath the wordmark, arranged side-by-side. Used for headers, primary branding surfaces, and any placement wide enough to accommodate the full lockup.

### Not Yet Finalized

A stacked lockup (icon above, wordmark below) was referenced in earlier concept work but has not been finalized or uploaded as an asset. It should not be treated as approved until a confirmed file exists. This document will be updated when it is.

## File Status

No production vector file (SVG/AI/EPS) currently exists. The available assets are PNG exports of the concept, at the resolutions and background variants noted above. Before this mark is used in production (app builds, printed packaging, signage), it should be redrawn or exported as a proper vector file — either by regenerating from the original design source or by commissioning a designer to vectorize the existing concept.

